JOHANNESBURG - A Gauteng Health Department official, who was instrumental in making decision regarding the Life Esidimeni patient transfers, was ordered to testify by the head of the arbitration hearings into the tradedy, retired deputy Chief Justice, Dikgang Moseneke.  On Monday, Doctor Makgabo Manamela's legal representative argued that her testimony should be postponed, because she required information presented at the hearings.  READ: Esidimeni: 'You could have asked for help', Moseneke tells nurse However, Moseneke rejected the argument and Manamela was forced to explain why mentally ill patients were moved from private healthcare facilities to unregistered NGOs. Manamela signed off on all the transfer documents.  Over 140 patients died following the transfers, many from starvation, dehydration and hypothermia.  eNCA